Wine Sauber auf Debian de- und installieren.

De-installation:

wine --version

sudo rm -rf /etc/apt/keyrings oder sudo rm /etc/apt/keyrings/winehq-archive.key

sudo rm /etc/apt/sources.list.d/winehq-trixie.sources

sudo apt remove --purge wine*
sudo apt remove --purge winetricks
sudo apt autoremove

rm ~/.wine

Installation:

sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386

cat /etc/os-release (Welche Version z.b. trixie)

sudo mkdir -pm755 /etc/apt/keyrings
wget -O - https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/winehq.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/winehq-archive.key -

Beispiel Trixie:

sudo wget -NP /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/debian/dists/trixie/winehq-trixie.sources

sudo apt update

sudo apt install --install-recommends winehq-stable

Konfiguration:

winecfg

winetricks explorer
winetricks corefonts
wine pfad/windowsprogramm.exe

WinePrefixes erstellen:
mkdir ~/name
WINEPREFIX=pfad_zum_prefix/ winecfg
WINEPREFIX=pfad_zum_prefix/ winetricks explorer


